OL,3,CCyber attack on Legal Aid Agency
OL,4,Cexposes 'significant amount' of
OL,5,Capplicant data
OL,7,FA "significant amount of personal
OL,8,Fdata" of people who applied to the
OL,9,FLegal Aid Agency since 2010 has been
OL,10,Faccessed and downloaded in a cyber
OL,11,Fattack, the Ministry of Justice (MoJ)
OL,12,Fsaid on Monday.
OL,14,FThe group that carried out the attack
OL,15,Fclaims it has accessed 2.1 million
OL,16,Fpieces of data, including applicants'
OL,17,Fcriminal records, but the MoJ has not
OL,18,Fverified that figure.
