OL,3,CCyber attack on Legal Aid Agency
OL,4,Cexposes 'significant amount' of
OL,5,Capplicant data
OL,7,FThe data accessed may include contact
OL,8,Fdetails and addresses of legal aid
OL,9,Fapplicants, their dates of birth,
OL,10,Fnational insurance numbers, criminal
OL,11,Fhistory, employment status and
OL,12,Ffinancial data such as contribution
OL,13,Famounts, debts and payments.
OL,15,FThe LAA's online digital services,
OL,16,Fwhich are used by legal aid providers
OL,17,Fto log their work and get paid by the
OL,18,FGovernment, have been taken offline.
